name: anaerobic digestion plant construction, agriculture, with methane recovery | anaerobic digestion plant, agriculture, with methane recovery | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/8733/documentation

The inventory refers to a typical agricultural biogas plant with a capacity of 500m3 and a life time of 20 years.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]



The process includes the production, transport and disposal of the main materials for an agricultural biogas plant.
category: F:Construction/42:Civil engineering/429:Construction of other civil engineering projects/4290:Construction of other civil engineering projects
tags: Sector: Infrastructure & Machinery; Agriculture & Animal Husbandry

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: This process refers to an agricultural biogas plant with a capacity of about 500m3. The data were sampled from 20 different plants in Switzerland.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: To avoid Methane emissions the new plants in Switzerland are covered.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: no extrapolation was necessary because the typical plants for the region and time period were evaluated This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography CH. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: The data are the average of 20 from 70 plants in Switzerland
